<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-pstpAgTfrfZhwkKwG2EN5g" name=",_jF8iUMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw" guid="-pstpAgTfrfZhwkKwG2EN5g" changeDate="2008-12-12T12:32:39.872+0100">
  <sections xmi:id="_zyKA8MhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Define how to evaluate candidate services having in mind strategic related aspects " guid="_zyKA8MhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>As in the task “Map services specifications with abstract descriptions”, developers have to define the metrics to evaluate which are the best options for each functional slice. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>The metrics defined before were at requirements marching level, but now there are other factors which are important like cost, provider, known results, extra features of the services, the possibility to use the same service for more than one functional slice or real needs for the composition (although a service offers better QoS levels than needed, it is possible that developers prefer to include a cheaper service with a lower QoS level because it is not necessary). &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Note: Some companies might have specific policies for this step. This means that the company could have defined the most important aspects of services from the organizational point of view. If these policies exist, have them in mind when evaluating candidates. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_0xfXAMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Evaluate each service to know which ones are the best options " guid="_0xfXAMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Evaluate each service according to the metrics defined calculating the score of each candidate. Do not forget to evaluate each service for each functional slice. Although these metrics are related to the global service characteristics, the score obtained about requirements matching has to be taken in account. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>For those services which implement a functional slice partially, do especial evaluation to obtain a compensated score. Remember that they can be good alternatives complemented with other services. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_2HoDgMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Put in order all the alternatives for each functional slice " guid="_2HoDgMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Arrange the services in a list in such a way that the first service will be the candidate to implement the functionality, while the rest of the services will be alternatives in case that the candidate fails, become unavailable, or implements only part of the functionality. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Note for companies which develop services: Companies which develop services can use the metrics to improve their developments focusing the effort in those issues which facilitate composition with other services. In this way, their services will obtain better scores in the evaluation, achieving higher positions in the rating. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;span&#xD;
style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>Once&#xD;
all the abstract tasks descriptions have been formalized and that the development team has a list of candidates, it is time&#xD;
to select which are going to be the services to be used and the services which could be used as a good alternative (in case&#xD;
there is an error, for instance).&lt;/span></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
